cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper describes a new framework for fitting large-scale physical models and performing statistical analysis. This involves handling large numbers of parameters and propagating uncertainties while taking into account possible correlations between them. These concepts are closely related to the fields of systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE).
